234
00:16:27,195 --> 00:16:30,039
<i>It was thought that these bridges
gradually disintegrated...</i>

235
00:16:30,198 --> 00:16:33,543
<i>...and vanished
beneath the waves long ago.</i>

236
00:16:33,701 --> 00:16:36,500
<i>But there was one piece of evidence
that convinced Wegener...</i>

237
00:16:36,662 --> 00:16:39,632
<i>...that the prevailing scientific view
must be wrong:</i>

238
00:16:39,790 --> 00:16:42,418
<i>the Earth itself.</i>

239
00:16:42,585 --> 00:16:45,429
<i>Why would a mountain range
cross the oceanic divide...</i>

240
00:16:45,588 --> 00:16:47,761
<i>...to continue on another continent?</i>

241
00:16:47,924 --> 00:16:50,268
<i>And why would you find
the same unique pattern...</i>

242
00:16:50,426 --> 00:16:54,226
<i>...in the layers of rocks
in both Brazil and South Africa?</i>

243
00:16:54,388 --> 00:16:58,768
<i>And another thing: Under what circumstances
could tropical plants have flourished...</i>

244
00:16:58,935 --> 00:17:02,189
<i>...in the frozen wastes of the Arctic?</i>

245
00:17:02,772 --> 00:17:06,902
<i>Wegener concluded that there was only
one logical solution to this puzzle:</i>

246
00:17:07,068 --> 00:17:10,618
<i>There had once been a single
supercontinent on Earth.</i>

247
00:17:10,780 --> 00:17:14,000
<i>He named it Pangaea.</i>

248
00:17:14,158 --> 00:17:18,413
So Wegener becomes the toast
of the scientific world, right?

249
00:17:18,579 --> 00:17:20,001
Not exactly.

250
00:17:20,164 --> 00:17:24,385
Most geologists ridiculed
Wegener's hypothesis of continental drift.

251
00:17:25,127 --> 00:17:28,381
They preferred
their imaginary natural land bridges...

252
00:17:28,548 --> 00:17:30,391
...to explain away Wegener's evidence.

253
00:17:32,301 --> 00:17:38,479
How, they asked, could a continent plow
through the solid rock of the ocean floor?

254
00:17:38,641 --> 00:17:41,315
Wegener had no convincing answer.

255
00:17:41,477 --> 00:17:46,483
He became the laughingstock of the field,
a pariah at scientific conferences.

256
00:17:46,649 --> 00:17:47,696
[DOGS BARKING]

257
00:17:47,858 --> 00:17:50,987
<i>Despite this,
Wegener continued to fight for his ideas...</i>

258
00:17:51,153 --> 00:17:55,579
<i>...conducting daring research expeditions
to gather evidence.</i>

259
00:17:55,741 --> 00:18:01,089
<i>On one of these, he learned that colleagues
